I taught Earth 194DE (
\f1\i Readings in Geoscience Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion
\f0\i0 ) in the UCSB Earth Science department in Spring of 2022 while I was a postdoc. This was the first offering of this class and represents a nice case study for the curriculum. This 3 unit course was an informal reading group open to undergraduates and graduate students, but closed to faculty, staff, and postdocs to keep the space more confidential. We met once a week for 1.5 hours. The night before, students would have 2-5 reflection questions about the 1-2 required papers. In class, we would start with serial testimony from the reflection questions, take a break, and then move to less structured discussion of the paper. \
\
I\'92ve included in this zip file: \
- Syllabus \
- Required readings (both with and without my annotations) \
- Additional readings \
- Weekly notes (including some discussion questions/prompts) \
- Relevant resources \
- Weekly reflection quizzes\
- Student evaluations \
\
Please feel free to use any of these materials to rework the class, reteach it, or just to find interesting papers. If you want to get in touch with any questions, my email is phillips.alexandra.a@gmail.com. \
