Thoughts on improvements for future iterations:\
\
- Serial testimony was a big hit! Had to adjust after a few weeks to have shorter or fewer questions though - this segment took 1/3 of each class, which felt like a good balance \
\
- Reading quizzes were also generally great, encouraged students to come to class having read the paper \
\
- It would be nice to have a 10th week next time if possible, where we could read about higher academic structures - like the paper one of the students presented on about diversity statements \
\
- I liked the student presentations a lot, but there wasn\'92t much time for discussion - may need to be revisited if a larger class size (perhaps in groups) \
\
- Dynamics may be hard to manage if taught by not a postdoc - may be hard to keep the safe space feeling with a professor teaching \
\
- Students expressed that were happy with the policy that they could miss one week of class - I still asked them to do the online reflections, but gave an extra 1-2 weeks for completion (some students ended up missing 2 weeks for excused reasons and that was also OK. Nobody missed more than 2)\
\
